            "title": "Loading",
            "content": [
                {
                    "name": "Destroy Image Resources Used by Texture",
                    "scene": "Loader/Loader_ClearTextureRes",
                    "desc": "Destroy the image resources used by Texture, retaining the texture shell. If it is found that the image resource used by texture does not exist when rendering next time, it will automatically recover; compared to clearRes, clearTextureRes just cleans up the image resources used inside the texture without destroying the texture, and can automatically recover the image resources when used again; whereas clearRes completely destroys the texture, causing it to be unusable; clearTextureRes ensures immediate destruction of image resources without worrying about destroying incorrectly, clearRes uses a reference count method for destruction;"
                },
